<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</emphasis>
Single specimen; lophophytous white sponge (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 60" captionStartId="F60" captionText="Figure 60. Bolosominae stet. CCZ _ 198 A, C in situ images B specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 5 cm (A, C). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A, C); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure60" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716386" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">60A, B</figureCitation>
). Body is cup- to bell-shaped, slightly wider than long (L = 10 cm, W = 11 cm), with a long, slender stalk (L = 70 cm) anchored to soft sediment. Central osculum with thick body walls.
</paragraph>
